{
  "answer": "**The title of the ghazal in chapter 100 of *Diwan-e-Ghalib* is \"Kaaba mein jaa raha toh na do ta'na kya kahein\".**[^1]\n\n**This is also the first *misra* (line) of the *matla* (opening couplet or *sher*), which reads in the original Urdu:**\n\n> کعبہ میں جا رہا تو نہ دو طعنہ کیا کہیں  \n> بھولا ہوں حقِ صحبتِ اہلِ کنشت کو[^2]\n\n**Transliteration:**  \nKaaba mein jaa raha toh na do ta'na kya kahein  \nBhoola hoon haq-e-sohbat-e-ahl-e-kunisht ko.[^3]\n\n**English translation:**  \nDon't mock my path toward the holy site, you see,  \nThe tavern's fellowship is lost to me.[^4]\n\nIn the structure of Ghalib's *Diwan*, each chapter represents one ghazal, titled by the *matla*'s first line.[^1]\n\n[^1]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 100, [translation](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/100-kaaba-mein-jaa-raha-toh-na-do-tana-kya-kahein/translation/).\n[^2]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 100, paragraph `p-87f275`, [original](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/100-kaaba-mein-jaa-raha-toh-na-do-tana-kya-kahein/original/#p-87f275).\n[^3]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 100, paragraph `p-eab6eb`, [transliteration](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/100-kaaba-mein-jaa-raha-toh-na-do-tana-kya-kahein/transliteration/#p-eab6eb).\n[^4]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 100, paragraph `p-fa6504`, [translation](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/100-kaaba-mein-jaa-raha-toh-na-do-tana-kya-kahein/translation/#p-fa6504).",
